{"_id":"6CYuPWcOprvP9Fr8","name":"Bone Golem","type":"monster","img":"modules/basicfantasyrpg-corerules-en/assets/tokens-monsters/bone-golem.png","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Golems are magically created automatons of great power. Constructing one involves the employment of mighty magic and elemental forces. The animating force for a golem is an elemental spirit. The process of creating the golem binds the spirit to the artificial body and subjects it to the will of the golem&rsquo;s creator.</p>\n<p>Being mindless, golems generally do nothing without orders from their creators. They follow instructions explicitly and are incapable of any strategy or tactics. A golem&rsquo;s creator can command it if the golem is within 60 feet and can see and hear its creator. If not actively commanded, a golem usually follows its last instruction to&nbsp;the best of its ability, though if attacked it returns the&nbsp;attack. The creator can give the golem a simple command&nbsp;to govern its actions in his or her absence. The golem&rsquo;s&nbsp;creator can order the golem to obey the commands of&nbsp;another person (who might in turn place the golem under&nbsp;someone else&rsquo;s control, and so on), but the golem&rsquo;s creator&nbsp;can always resume control over his creation by&nbsp;commanding the golem to obey him alone.</p>\n<p>Golems have immunity to most magical and supernatural effects, except when otherwise noted. They can only be hit by magical weapons.</p>\n<p>Bone golems are huge four-armed monsters created from the skeletons of at least two dead humanoids. Though made of bone, they are not undead and cannot be turned.</p>\n<p>Instead of four one-handed weapons, a bone golem can be armed with two two-handed weapons, giving 2 attacks per round and a damage figure of 1d10/1d10 or by weapon.</p>\n<p>When a bone golem enters combat, there is a cumulative 1% chance each round that its elemental spirit breaks free and the golem goes berserk. The uncontrolled golem goes on a rampage, attacking the nearest living creature or smashing some object smaller than itself if no creature is within reach, then moving on to spread more destruction. The golem&rsquo;s creator, if within 60 feet, can try to regain control by speaking firmly and persuasively to the golem; he or she must make a save vs. Spells to succeed at this, and at least 1 round of time is required for each check. It takes 1 round of inactivity by the golem to reset the golem&rsquo;s berserk chance to 0%.</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Bone Golem","img":"modules/basicfantasyrpg-corerules-en/assets/tokens-monsters/bone-golem.png","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":"hitPoints"},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"AesZk8pWQwdPEnG7","name":"Amber Golem","type":"monster","img":"modules/basicfantasyrpg-corerules-en/assets/tokens-monsters/amber-golem.png","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Golems are magically created automatons of great power. Constructing one involves the employment of mighty magic and elemental forces. The animating force for a golem is an elemental spirit. The process of creating the golem binds the spirit to the artificial body and subjects it to the will of the golem&rsquo;s creator.</p>\n<p>Being mindless, golems generally do nothing without orders from their creators. They follow instructions explicitly and are incapable of any strategy or tactics. A golem&rsquo;s creator can command it if the golem is within 60 feet and can see and hear its creator. If not actively commanded, a golem usually follows its last instruction to&nbsp;the best of its ability, though if attacked it returns the&nbsp;attack. The creator can give the golem a simple command&nbsp;to govern its actions in his or her absence. The golem&rsquo;s&nbsp;creator can order the golem to obey the commands of&nbsp;another person (who might in turn place the golem under&nbsp;someone else&rsquo;s control, and so on), but the golem&rsquo;s creator&nbsp;can always resume control over his creation by&nbsp;commanding the golem to obey him alone.</p>\n<p>Golems have immunity to most magical and supernatural effects, except when otherwise noted. They can only be hit by magical weapons.</p>\n<p>Amber golems are generally built to resemble lions or other great cats. They are able to detect invisible creatures or objects within 60', and can track with 95% accuracy through any terrain type.</p>\n<p>A magical attack that deals electricity damage heals 1 point of damage for every 3 full points of damage the attack would otherwise deal. For example, an amber golem hit by a <strong>lightning bolt</strong> for 20 points of damage is instead healed up to 6 points. If the amount of healing would cause the golem to exceed its full normal hit points, the excess is ignored.</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Amber Golem","img":"modules/basicfantasyrpg-corerules-en/assets/tokens-monsters/amber-golem.png","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":"hitPoints"},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ClzmJV4VGjhP2QPd","name":"Stone Living Statue","type":"monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Living statues are magically animated. They are true&nbsp;automatons, unlike golems, which are animated by&nbsp;elemental spirits. While this means that living statues have&nbsp;no chance of going &ldquo;berserk,&rdquo; it also means that they may&nbsp;only perform simple programmed activities. They may not&nbsp;be commanded in any meaningful fashion. They make&nbsp;very effective guards for tombs, treasure rooms, and&nbsp;similar places.</p>\n<p>Living statues can be crafted to resemble any sort of living&nbsp;creature, but most commonly are made to look like&nbsp;humans or demi-humans.</p>\n<p>A stone living statue attacks by spraying molten rock from its fingertips. The range of the spray is 5'.</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Stone Living Statue","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":"hitPoints"},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"JfSnSGOpqnJgqNgU","name":"Crystal Living Statue","type":"monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Living statues are magically animated. They are true automatons, unlike golems, which are animated by elemental spirits. While this means that living statues have no chance of going &ldquo;berserk,&rdquo; it also means that they may only perform simple programmed activities. They may not be commanded in any meaningful fashion. They make very effective guards for tombs, treasure rooms, and similar places.</p>\n<p>Living statues can be crafted to resemble any sort of living creature, but most commonly are made to look like humans or demi-humans.</p>\n<p>Crystal living statues have no particular special powers, unlike those made of iron or stone.</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Crystal Living Statue","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mi