{"_id":"OGPdDTNyvgu1ffl3","name":"Iron Living Statue","type":"monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Living statues are magically animated. They are true&nbsp;automatons, unlike golems, which are animated by&nbsp;elemental spirits. While this means that living statues have&nbsp;no chance of going &ldquo;berserk,&rdquo; it also means that they may&nbsp;only perform simple programmed activities. They may not&nbsp;be commanded in any meaningful fashion. They make&nbsp;very effective guards for tombs, treasure rooms, and&nbsp;similar places.</p>\n<p>Living statues can be crafted to resemble any sort of living&nbsp;creature, but most commonly are made to look like&nbsp;humans or demi-humans.</p>\n<p>If struck by a non-magical metal (even partially metal)&nbsp;weapon, the weapon may become stuck in the monster. If&nbsp;this happens, it cannot be removed until the statue is &ldquo;killed.&rdquo; The wielder is allowed a save vs. Spells to avoid&nbsp;this.&nbsp;</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Iron Living Statue","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":"hitPoints"},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"R0sgVRLNFU7wXQjJ","name":"Wood Golem","type":"monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Golems are magically created automatons of great power. Constructing one involves the employment of mighty magic and elemental forces. The animating force for a golem is an elemental spirit. The process of creating the golem binds the spirit to the artificial body and subjects it to the will of the golem&rsquo;s creator.</p>\n<p>Being mindless, golems generally do nothing without orders from their creators. They follow instructions explicitly and are incapable of any strategy or tactics. A golem&rsquo;s creator can command it if the golem is within 60 feet and can see and hear its creator. If not actively commanded, a golem usually follows its last instruction to the best of its ability, though if attacked it returns the attack. The creator can give the golem a simple command to govern its actions in his or her absence. The golem&rsquo;s creator can order the golem to obey the commands of another person (who might in turn place the golem under someone else&rsquo;s control, and so on), but the golem&rsquo;s creator can always resume control over his creation by commanding the golem to obey him alone.</p>\n<p>Golems have immunity to most magical and supernatural effects, except when otherwise noted. They can only be hit by magical weapons.</p>\n<p>Wood golems are small constructs, not more than 4' in height, and are crudely made. Being made of wood makes them vulnerable to fire-based attacks; thus, wood golems suffer one extra point of damage per die from fire; any saving throws against such effects are at a penalty of -2. They move stiffly, suffering a -1 penalty to Initiative.</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Wood Golem","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":"hitPoints"},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"YcfUJiZ877IoNpUb","name":"Flesh Golem","type":"monster","img":"modules/basicfantasyrpg-corerules-en/assets/tokens-monsters/flesh-golem.png","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Golems are magically created automatons of great power. Constructing one involves the employment of mighty magic and elemental forces. The animating force for a golem is an elemental spirit. The process of creating the golem binds the spirit to the artificial body and subjects it to the will of the golem&rsquo;s creator.</p>\n<p>Being mindless, golems generally do nothing without orders from their creators. They follow instructions explicitly and are incapable of any strategy or tactics. A golem&rsquo;s creator can command it if the golem is within 60 feet and can see and hear its creator. If not actively commanded, a golem usually follows its last instruction to&nbsp;the best of its ability, though if attacked it returns the&nbsp;attack. The creator can give the golem a simple command&nbsp;to govern its actions in his or her absence. The golem&rsquo;s&nbsp;creator can order the golem to obey the commands of&nbsp;another person (who might in turn place the golem under&nbsp;someone else&rsquo;s control, and so on), but the golem&rsquo;s creator&nbsp;can always resume control over his creation by&nbsp;commanding the golem to obey him alone.</p>\n<p>Golems have immunity to most magical and supernatural effects, except when otherwise noted. They can only be hit by magical weapons.</p>\n<p>A flesh golem is a ghoulish collection of stolen humanoid body parts, stitched together into a single composite form. No natural animal willingly tracks a flesh golem. The golem wears whatever clothing its creator desires, usually just a ragged pair of trousers. It has no possessions and no weapons. It stands 8 feet tall and weighs almost 500 pounds. A flesh golem cannot speak, although it can emit a hoarse roar of sorts. It walks and moves with a stiff-jointed gait, as if not in complete control of its body.</p>\n<p>When a flesh golem enters combat, there is a cumulative 1% chance each round that its elemental spirit will break free. Such a golem will go on a rampage, attacking the nearest living creature or smashing some object smaller than itself if no creature is within reach, then moving on to cause more destruction. The golem&rsquo;s creator, if within 60 feet, can try to regain control by speaking firmly and persuasively to the golem; he or she must make a save vs. Spells to succeed at this, and at least 1 round of time is required for each check. It takes 1 round of inactivity by the golem to reset the golem&rsquo;s berserk chance to 0%.</p>\n<p>A magical attack that deals cold or fire damage slows a flesh golem (as the <strong>slow</strong> spell) for 2d6 rounds, with no saving throw. A magical attack that deals electricity damage breaks any slow effect on the golem and heals 1 point of damage for every 3 full points of damage the attack would otherwise deal. If the amount of healing would cause the golem to exceed its full normal hit points, the excess is ignored. For example, a flesh golem hit by a lightning bolt heals 3 points of damage if the attack would have dealt 11 points of damage.</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Flesh Golem","img":"modules/basicfantasyrpg-corerules-en/assets/tokens-monsters/flesh-golem.png","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":"hitPoints"},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"cr1r8vvsmmNtnJOW","name":"Iron Golem","type":"monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Golems are magically created automatons of great power. Constructing one involves the employment of mighty magic and elemental forces. The animating force for a golem is an elemental spirit. The process of creating the golem binds the spirit to the artificial body and subjects it to the will of the golem&rsquo;s creator.</p>\n<p>Being mindless, golems generally do nothing without orders from their creators. They follow instructions explicitly and are incapable of any strategy or tactics. A golem&rsquo;s creator can command it if the golem is within 60 feet and can see and hear its creator. If not actively commanded, a golem usually follows its last instruction to&nbsp;the best of its ability, though if attacked it returns the&nbsp;attack. The creator can give the golem a simple command&nbsp;to govern its actions in his or her absence. The golem&rsquo;s&nbsp;creator can order the golem to obey the commands of&nbsp;another person (who might in turn place the golem under&nbsp;someone else&rsquo;s control, and so on), but the golem&rsquo;s creator&nbsp;can always resume control over his creation by&nbsp;commanding the golem to obey him alone.</p>\n<p>Golems have immunity to most magical and supernatural effects, except when otherwise noted. They can only be hit by magical weapons.</p>\n<p>This golem has a humanoid body made from iron. An iron golem can be fashioned in any manner, just like a stone golem (see below), although it almost always displays armor of some sort. Its features are much smoother than those of a stone golem. Iron golems sometimes carry a short sword in one hand. An iron golem is 12 feet tall and weighs about 5,000 pounds. An iron golem cannot speak or make any vocal noise, nor does it have any distinguishable odor. It moves with a ponderous but smooth gait. Each step causes the floor to tremble unless it is on a thick, solid foundation.</p>\n<p>Iron golems can exhale a cloud of poisonous gas which fills a 10-foot cube and persists for 1 round. Those within the area of effect must save vs. Dragon Breath or die. This ability can be used up to 3 times per day.</p>\n<p>A magical attack that deals electricity damage slows an iron golem (as the <strong>slow</strong> spell) for 3 rounds, with no saving throw. A magical attack that deals fire damage breaks any slow effect on the golem and heals 1 point of damage for each 3 full points of damage the attack would otherwise deal. If the amount of healing would cause the golem to exceed its full normal hit points, the excess is ignored. For example, an iron golem hit by a fireball gains back 6 hit points if the damage total is 19 points. An iron golem is affected normally by rust attacks, such as that of a rust monster, suffering 2d6 points of damage for each hit (with no saving throw normally allowed).</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Iron Golem","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":"hitPoints"},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ePCkndT5ySJh1vcU","name":"Clay Golem","type":"monster","img":"modules/basicfantasyrpg-corerules-en/assets/tokens-monsters/clay-golem.png","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Golems are magically created automatons of great power. Constructing one involves the employment of mighty magic and elemental forces. The animating force for a golem is an elemental spirit. The process of creating the golem binds the spirit to the artificial body and subjects it to the will of the golem&rsquo;s creator.</p>\n<p>Being mindless, golems generally do nothing without orders from their creators. They follow instructions explicitly and are incapable of any strategy or tactics. A golem&rsquo;s creator can command it if the golem is within 60 feet and can see and hear its creator. If not actively commanded, a golem usually follows its last instruction to&nbsp;the best of its ability, though if attacked it returns the&nbsp;attack. The creator can give the golem a simple command&nbsp;to govern its actions in his or her absence. The golem&rsquo;s&nbsp;creator can order the golem to obey the commands of&nbsp;another person (who might in turn place the golem under&nbsp;someone else&rsquo;s control, and so on), but the golem&rsquo;s creator&nbsp;can always resume control over his creation by&nbsp;commanding the golem to obey him alone.</p>\n<p>Golems have immunity to most magical and supernatural effects, except when otherwise noted. They can only be hit by magical weapons.</p>\n<p>This golem has a humanoid body made from clay. A clay golem wears no clothing except for a metal or stiff leather garment around its hips. A clay golem cannot speak or make any vocal noise. It walks and moves with a slow, clumsy gait. It weighs around 600 pounds.</p>\n<p>When a clay golem enters combat, there is a cumulative 1% chance each round that its elemental spirit will break free. Such a golem will go on a rampage, attacking the nearest living creature or smashing some object smaller than itself if no creature is within reach, then moving on to cause more destruction. Once a clay golem goes berserk, no known method can reestablish control.</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Clay Golem","img":"modules/basicfantasyrpg-corerules-en/assets/tokens-monsters/clay-golem.png","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":"hitPoints"},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ijf6gMptM34C1GO7","name":"Bronze Golem","type":"monster","img":"modules/basicfantasyrpg-corerules-en/assets/tokens-monsters/bronze-golem.png","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Golems are magically created automatons of great power. Constructing one involves the employment of mighty magic and elemental forces. The animating force for a golem is an elemental spirit. The process of creating the golem binds the spirit to the artificial body and subjects it to the will of the golem&rsquo;s creator.</p>\n<p>Being mindless, golems generally do nothing without orders from their creators. They follow instructions explicitly and are incapable of any strategy or tactics. A golem&rsquo;s creator can command it if the golem is within 60 feet and can see and hear its creator. If not actively commanded, a golem usually follows its last instruction to&nbsp;the best of its ability, though if attacked it returns the&nbsp;attack. The creator can give the golem a simple command&nbsp;to govern its actions in his or her absence. The golem&rsquo;s&nbsp;creator can order the golem to obey the commands of&nbsp;another person (who might in turn place the golem under&nbsp;someone else&rsquo;s control, and so on), but the golem&rsquo;s creator&nbsp;can always resume control over his creation by&nbsp;commanding the golem to obey him alone.</p>\n<p>Golems have immunity to most magical and supernatural effects, except when otherwise noted. They can only be hit by magical weapons.</p>\n<p>These golems resemble statues made of bronze; unlike natural bronze statues, they never turn green from verdigris. A bronze golem is 10 feet tall and weighs about 4,500 pounds. A bronze golem cannot speak or make any vocal noise, nor does it have any distinguishable odor. It moves with a ponderous but smooth gait. Each step causes the floor to tremble unless it is on a thick, solid foundation.</p>\n<p>The interior of a bronze golem is molten metal. Creatures hit by one in combat suffer an additional 1d10 damage from the heat (unless resistant to heat or fire). If one is hit in combat, molten metal spurts out, spraying the attacker for 2d6 damage. A save vs. Death Ray is allowed to avoid the metal spray.</p>\n<p>When a bronze golem enters combat, there is a cumulative 1% chance each round that its elemental spirit will break free. Such a golem will go on a rampage, attacking the nearest living creature or smashing some object smaller than itself if no creature is within reach, then moving on to cause more destruction. The golem&rsquo;s creator, if within 60 feet, can try to regain control by speaking firmly and persuasively to the golem; he or she must make a save vs. Spells to succeed at this, and at least 1 round of time is required for each check. It takes 1 round of inactivity by the golem to reset the chance it will go berserk to 0%.</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Bronze Golem","img":"modules/basicfantasyrpg-corerules-en/assets/tokens-monsters/bronze-golem.png","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":"hitPoints"},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"nqUY4sh31bsJiheA","name":"Stone Golem","type":"monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"armorClass":{"value":11,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClass","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ArmorClassAbbr"},"attackBonus":{"value":1,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonus","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.AttackBonusAbbr"},"biography":"<p>Golems are magically created automatons of great power. Constructing one involves the employment of mighty magic and elemental forces. The animating force for a golem is an elemental spirit. The process of creating the golem binds the spirit to the artificial body and subjects it to the will of the golem&rsquo;s creator.</p>\n<p>Being mindless, golems generally do nothing without orders from their creators. They follow instructions explicitly and are incapable of any strategy or tactics. A golem&rsquo;s creator can command it if the golem is within 60 feet and can see and hear its creator. If not actively commanded, a golem usually follows its last instruction to&nbsp;the best of its ability, though if attacked it returns the&nbsp;attack. The creator can give the golem a simple command&nbsp;to govern its actions in his or her absence. The golem&rsquo;s&nbsp;creator can order the golem to obey the commands of&nbsp;another person (who might in turn place the golem under&nbsp;someone else&rsquo;s control, and so on), but the golem&rsquo;s creator&nbsp;can always resume control over his creation by&nbsp;commanding the golem to obey him alone.</p>\n<p>Golems have immunity to most magical and supernatural&nbsp;effects, except when otherwise noted. They can only be&nbsp;hit by magical weapons.</p>\n<p>This golem has a humanoid body made from stone. A stone golem is 9 feet tall and weighs around 2,000 pounds. Its body is frequently stylized to suit its creator. For example, it might look like it is wearing armor, with a particular symbol carved on the breastplate, or have designs worked into the stone of its limbs.</p>\n<p>Stone golems are formidable opponents, being physically powerful and difficult to harm. A stone golem can use a <strong>slow</strong> effect, as the spell, once every other round; a save vs. Spells is allowed to resist. The effect has a range of 10 feet and a duration of 2d6 rounds.</p>\n<p>A <strong>stone to flesh</strong> spell may be used to weaken the monster. The spell does not actually change the golem&rsquo;s structure, but for one full round after being affected, the golem is vulnerable to normal weapons. The stone golem is allowed a save vs. Spells to resist this effect.</p>","hitPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitPointsAbbr"},"initBonus":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.InitiativeBonus"},"move":{"value":"30","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Movement"},"saves":{"death":{"value":13},"wands":{"value":14},"paralysis":{"value":15},"breath":{"value":16},"spells":{"value":18}},"hitDice":{"size":"d8","number":1,"mod":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDice","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.HitDiceAbbr"},"morale":{"value":7,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Morale"},"numberAppearing":{"value":"1d4","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.NumberAppearing"},"specialAbility":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpecialAbility"},"treasureType":{"value":"None","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.TreasureType"},"xp":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePoints","abbr":"BASICFANTASYRPG.ExperiencePointsAbbr"}},"token":{"name":"Stone Golem","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":"hitPoints"},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"r